abstract: The Trump administration plans to stick with its proposed 2020 biofuel blending requirements, the White House said on Wednesday, despite anger among farmers that the plan does too little for corn growers.
snippet: The Trump administration plans to stick with its proposed 2020 biofuel blending requirements, the White House said on Wednesday, despite anger among farmers that the plan does too little for corn growers.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Trump administration plans to stick with its proposed 2020 biofuel blending requirements, the White House said on Wednesday, despite anger among farmers that the plan does too little for corn growers.
headline_main: White House Says It Is Sticking With 2020 Biofuel Plan, Despite Farmer Objections
headline_print_headline: White House Says It Is Sticking With 2020 Biofuel Plan, Despite Farmer Objections

abstract: The U.S. Senate Foreign Relations Committee approved legislation on Wednesday that would impose sanctions on Russia, but there was no indication of when the full Senate might vote on the measure that one sponsor called the sanctions bill "from hell."
snippet: The U.S. Senate Foreign Relations Committee approved legislation on Wednesday that would impose sanctions on Russia, but there was no indication of when the full Senate might vote on the measure that one sponsor called the sanctions bill "from hel...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate Foreign Relations Committee approved legislation on Wednesday that would impose sanctions on Russia, but there was no indication of when the full Senate might vote on the measure that one sponsor called the sanctions bill "from hell."
headline_main: Senate Panel Advances Russia Sanctions Bill 'From Hell'
headline_print_headline: Senate Panel Advances Russia Sanctions Bill 'From Hell'

abstract: The United States and India agreed on Wednesday to expand defense, science and technology cooperation as Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said impeachment would not distract the Trump administration on national security matters
snippet: The United States and India agreed on Wednesday to expand defense, science and technology cooperation as Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said impeachment would not distract the Trump administration on national security matters
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States and India agreed on Wednesday to expand defense, science and technology cooperation as Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said impeachment would not distract the Trump administration on national security matters
headline_main: US and India Pledge Cooperation as Domestic Crises Play Out
headline_print_headline: US and India Pledge Cooperation as Domestic Crises Play Out

abstract: A bill to defend U.S. national security against Russia looks like an artifact from a different age — 10 months ago — when both parties agreed on the threat from Moscow.
snippet: A bill to defend U.S. national security against Russia looks like an artifact from a different age — 10 months ago — when both parties agreed on the threat from Moscow.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the House of Representatives began debating Wednesday whether to impeach President Trump for undercutting Ukraine in its fight with Russian aggressors, the Senate Foreign Relations Committee met in a small room in the Capitol to consider a bill that has been bubbling along all year with bipartisan support: S. 482, the “Defending American Security From Kremlin Aggression Act of 2019.”

abstract: A lawyer for a Ukrainian oligarch on Wednesday said he had lent $1 million to Lev Parnas, an associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani, and Parnas' wife in order for them to buy a home in Florida.
snippet: A lawyer for a Ukrainian oligarch on Wednesday said he had lent $1 million to Lev Parnas, an associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani, and Parnas' wife in order for them to buy a home in Florida.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI — A lawyer for a Ukrainian oligarch on Wednesday said he had lent $1 million to Lev Parnas, an associate of U.S. President Donald Trump's personal lawyer Rudy Giuliani, and Parnas' wife in order for them to buy a home in Florida.
headline_main: Exclusive: Ukrainian Tycoon's Lawyer Says He Lent Money to Giuliani Associate
headline_print_headline: Exclusive: Ukrainian Tycoon's Lawyer Says He Lent Money to Giuliani Associate

abstract: The Democratic-controlled U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to formally charge President Donald Trump, a Republican, with "high crimes and misdemeanors," making him only the third U.S. president in history to be impeached.
snippet: The Democratic-controlled U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to formally charge President Donald Trump, a Republican, with "high crimes and misdemeanors," making him only the third U.S. president in history to be impeached.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic-controlled U.S. House of Representatives will vote on Wednesday to formally charge President Donald Trump, a Republican, with "high crimes and misdemeanors," making him only the third U.S. president in history to be impeached.

abstract: The decision was a setback to efforts by a district attorney to ensure Mr. Manafort would still face prison time if President Trump pardoned him.
snippet: The decision was a setback to efforts by a district attorney to ensure Mr. Manafort would still face prison time if President Trump pardoned him.
lead_paragraph: A New York judge on Wednesday threw out state fraud charges against Paul J. Manafort, President Trump’s former campaign chairman, dealing a setback to efforts by the Manhattan district attorney to ensure Mr. Manafort would still face prosecution should Mr. Trump pardon him for his federal crimes.

headline_main: State Charges Against Manafort Dismissed by Judge in New York
headline_print_headline: Double Jeopardy Law  Ends Manafort Case

abstract: A New York judge threw out state mortgage fraud charges against Paul Manafort, ruling Wednesday that the criminal case was too similar to one that has already landed President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman in federal prison.
snippet: A New York judge threw out state mortgage fraud charges against Paul Manafort, ruling Wednesday that the criminal case was too similar to one that has already landed President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman in federal prison.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A New York judge threw out state mortgage fraud charges against Paul Manafort, ruling Wednesday that the criminal case was too similar to one that has already landed President Donald Trump's former campaign chairman in federal prison.
headline_main: Manafort's NY Fraud Case Tossed Over Double Jeopardy Concern
headline_print_headline: Manafort's NY Fraud Case Tossed Over Double Jeopardy Concern

abstract: The social-media sensei and advertising executive has found a side hustle playing both mentor and middleman between hip-hop artists and brands.

abstract: The Trump administration aims to stick with its current proposal on 2020 biofuel blending requirements, despite anger in Farm Country that the plan fails to compensate for the administration's expanded use of refinery waivers, according to two sources familiar with the matter.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Trump administration aims to stick with its current proposal on 2020 biofuel blending requirements, despite anger in Farm Country that the plan fails to compensate for the administration's expanded use of refinery waivers, according to two sources familiar with the matter.
headline_main: Exclusive: Trump Administration to Stick With 2020 Biofuel Plan Over Farmer Objections-Sources
